  <h2 class="entrydate">
    December 18, 2008  </h2>   <h3 class="entrytitle" id="post-995"> <a href="http://longorshortcapital.com/what-quality-due-diligence-looks-like.htm" rel="bookmark">
    What Quality Due Diligence Looks Like    </a> </h3>    


  <div class="entrybody">
    <p><center><img src="http://longorshortcapital.com/wp-content/fgg_due_diligence.jpg" alt="Fairfield Greenwich Group"/></center></p>
<p>As a follow-on to my previous post, I wanted to give investors an idea of what quality due diligence looks like in a handy to read chart.  This is exactly the kind of process that would ensure that investors are the victims of neither investment mismanagement nor fraud.  Hat tip for the picture to a firm called <a href="https://www.fggus.com/guest/due_diligence.html" class="broken_link">Fairfield Greenwich Group</a>.  </p>
